Scripts to make a working chroot on Mac OS X.
It currently works with Yosemite (10.10.1).

$ uname -a
Darwin lomidrevo.local 14.0.0 Darwin Kernel Version 14.0.0: Fri Sep 19 00:26:44 PDT 2014; root:xnu-2782.1.97~2/RELEASE_X86_64 x86_64

USAGE
=====

./mkmacchroot.sh [directory]

If the directory is not specified, then $PWD/mac-jail will be used.

./chroot.sh [directory]

This script enters the chroot as current user, re-using SSH agent
and mDNSResolver from host system.
